(43161143000); Moningi, Shalini (18038021200); Qian, Jack M. (57125301900); Goldstein, Madeleine (58546543500); Harper, Susan (58546829200); Aerts, Hugo J. W. L. (16479697600); Catalano, Paul J. (7101947533); Savova, Guergana K. (8312093900); Mak, Raymond H. (8597064200); Bitterman, Danielle S. (56307969500)
Title: Large language models to identify social determinants of health in electronic health records
Open Access: All Open Access; Gold Open Access
Primary Task: SDoH Entity Classification: employment, housing, transportation, parental status, relationship, and social support
PET Notes: Prompt ChatGPT for 538 Synthetic Sentences, 480 of which had SODH mentions and 289 had adverse SDOH mentions
Unnamed: 43: Compare task performance with synthetic notes added
Model: BERT-base, FLAN-T5 family, Zero-shot and Few Shot GPT 3.5, 4
Evaluation Data: MIMIC-III Test Set and OOD, real immunotherapy clinical notes
Summary: Investigate SDoH Entity Classification for LMs that add ChatGPT-generated notes to real clinical notes; and a bias evaluation of demographic injections to synthetic notes
Conclusion: Variable impact on Macro F1 performance, significant in smaller FLAN ; LLMs more susceptible to change from demographic injections to synthetic samples
